<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>England have claimed the T20 series against Australia as Jos Buttler's 77 not out powered them to a six-wicket victory over their rivals on Sunday.</p>

<p>Buttler racked up the runs with some impressive boundaries at the Ageas Bowl, as Moeen Ali joined him late on with a crucial six.</p>

<p>The hosts survived a late scare as Eoin Morgan was caught for seven with less than 20 balls left for the Aussies. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>England won their second Test against Australia to claim the T20 series in Southampton</p>

<p>Jos Buttler impressed at the Ageas Bowl as he scored 77 runs as he led England to victory</p>
